This paper focuses on analyzing online communities and their impact on mental health, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.SOC). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques to analyze conversation threads, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves building a classifier to predict outcomes, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves studying human-computer interaction in the context of mental health, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
